from fastcore.all import Path
from nbdev.export import Config
from torchvision.datasets import CIFAR10

from gale.classification.data.common import show_image_batch
from gale.classification.data.transforms import aug_transforms
from gale.collections.download import download_and_extract_archive

URL = "https://download.pytorch.org/tutorial/hymenoptera_data.zip"
data_path = Path(Config().path("nbs_path")) / "data"

register_torchvision_dataset[source]

register_torchvision_dataset(name:str, dataset:Dataset, mapper:Optional[Callable]=None, augmentations:Union[Compose, Compose, NoneType]=None, mean:Sequence[float]=(0.485, 0.456, 0.406), std:Sequence[float]=(0.229, 0.224, 0.225), xtras:Optional[Callable]=noop)

Register a dataset in gale DatasetCatalog from a existing torchvision dataset. You can pass in augmentations to specify the transformations you want to apply to the Images in the dataset. Optionaly, mapper can also be passed in or else the default ClassificationMapper will be used to map the dataset in gale ClassificationDataset format.

name is a str that identifies a dataset, e.g. "coco_2014_train".

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
dset = CIFAR10(data_path, download=True)

# create you transforms
aug_tfms = aug_transforms(70, 64, hflip=0.5, vflip=0.5, mult=2)

# now register the dataset to gale DatasetCataLog
register_torchvision_dataset("cifar_10", dset, augmentations=aug_tfms)

build_classification_loader_from_config[source]

build_classification_loader_from_config(name:str, config:DictConfig)

Build DataLoader from gale config using a dataset registerd in DatasetCatalog identified by name.

Arguments:

  1. name (str): represents the name of the registerd dataset.
  2. config (DictConfig): gale config for a dataloader.
{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from gale.config import get_config

cfg = get_config("classification")
cfg.datasets.train = "hymenoptera_train_v0"
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
dls = build_classification_loader_from_config(cfg.datasets.train, cfg.dataloader.train)

assert isinstance(dls, DataLoader)
show_image_batch(next(iter(dls)))
